    "body": "After further inspecting the code, implementing websockets might be more complicated than what I thought at first.\r\n\r\nI thought it would be enough to use the [*ethers*](https://docs.ethers.io/v5/api/providers/other/#WebSocketProvider) or [*web3*](https://web3py.readthedocs.io/en/stable/providers.html#websocketprovider) functions for sockets, but apparently Hardhat uses its own client for requests (see method `_fetchJsonRpcResponse`), which relies on [*node-fetch*](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-fetch) which in turn [does not support Websockets](https://github.com/whatwg/fetch/issues/235).\r\n\r\nI amÂ probably missing something here, as I was expecting Hardhat to use the same clients as Ethers/Web3.",
